name: min_compress_block_size
description: The actual size of the block to compress, if the uncompressed data less than max_compress_block_size is no less than this value and no less than the volume of data for one mark.

name: max_compress_block_size
description: The maximum size of blocks of uncompressed data before compressing for writing to a table.

name: max_block_size
description: Maximum block size for reading

name: max_insert_block_size
description: The maximum block size for insertion, if we control the creation of blocks for insertion.

name: min_insert_block_size_rows
description: Squash blocks passed to INSERT query to specified size in rows, if blocks are not big enough.

name: min_insert_block_size_bytes
description: Squash blocks passed to INSERT query to specified size in bytes, if blocks are not big enough.

name: min_insert_block_size_rows_for_materialized_views
description: Like min_insert_block_size_rows, but applied only during pushing to MATERIALIZED VIEW (default: min_insert_block_size_rows)

name: min_insert_block_size_bytes_for_materialized_views
description: Like min_insert_block_size_bytes, but applied only during pushing to MATERIALIZED VIEW (default: min_insert_block_size_bytes)

name: max_joined_block_size_rows
description: Maximum block size for JOIN result (if join algorithm supports it). 0 means unlimited.

name: max_insert_threads
description: The maximum number of threads to execute the INSERT SELECT query. Values 0 or 1 means that INSERT SELECT is not run in parallel. Higher values will lead to higher memory usage. Parallel INSERT SELECT has effect only if the SELECT part is run on parallel, see 'max_threads' setting.

name: max_final_threads
description: The maximum number of threads to read from table with FINAL.

name: max_threads
description: The maximum number of threads to execute the request. By default, it is determined automatically.

name: max_alter_threads
description: The maximum number of threads to execute the ALTER requests. By default, it is determined automatically.

name: max_read_buffer_size
description: The maximum size of the buffer to read from the filesystem.

name: max_distributed_connections
description: The maximum number of connections for distributed processing of one query (should be greater than max_threads).

name: max_query_size
description: Which part of the query can be read into RAM for parsing (the remaining data for INSERT, if any, is read later)

name: interactive_delay
description: The interval in microseconds to check if the request is cancelled, and to send progress info.

name: connect_timeout
description: Connection timeout if there are no replicas.

name: connect_timeout_with_failover_ms
description: Connection timeout for selecting first healthy replica.

name: connect_timeout_with_failover_secure_ms
description: Connection timeout for selecting first healthy replica (for secure connections).

name: tcp_keep_alive_timeout
description: The time in seconds the connection needs to remain idle before TCP starts sending keepalive probes

name: hedged_connection_timeout_ms
description: Connection timeout for establishing connection with replica for Hedged requests

name: receive_data_timeout_ms
description: Connection timeout for receiving first packet of data or packet with positive progress from replica

name: use_hedged_requests
description: Use hedged requests for distributed queries

name: allow_changing_replica_until_first_data_packet
description: Allow HedgedConnections to change replica until receiving first data packet

name: queue_max_wait_ms
description: The wait time in the request queue, if the number of concurrent requests exceeds the maximum.

name: connection_pool_max_wait_ms
description: The wait time when the connection pool is full.

name: replace_running_query_max_wait_ms
description: The wait time for running query with the same query_id to finish when setting 'replace_running_query' is active.

name: kafka_max_wait_ms
description: The wait time for reading from Kafka before retry.

name: rabbitmq_max_wait_ms
description: The wait time for reading from RabbitMQ before retry.

name: poll_interval
description: Block at the query wait loop on the server for the specified number of seconds.

name: idle_connection_timeout
description: Close idle TCP connections after specified number of seconds.

name: distributed_connections_pool_size
description: Maximum number of connections with one remote server in the pool.

name: connections_with_failover_max_tries
description: The maximum number of attempts to connect to replicas.

name: s3_min_upload_part_size
description: The minimum size of part to upload during multipart upload to S3.

name: s3_max_single_part_upload_size
description: The maximum size of object to upload using singlepart upload to S3.

name: s3_max_single_read_retries
description: The maximum number of retries during single S3 read.

name: s3_max_redirects
description: Max number of S3 redirects hops allowed.

name: s3_max_connections
description: The maximum number of connections per server.

name: hsts_max_age
description: Expired time for hsts. 0 means disable HSTS.

name: extremes
description: Calculate minimums and maximums of the result columns. They can be output in JSON-formats.

name: use_uncompressed_cache
description: Whether to use the cache of uncompressed blocks.

name: replace_running_query
description: Whether the running request should be canceled with the same id as the new one.

name: background_buffer_flush_schedule_pool_size
description: Number of threads performing background flush for tables with Buffer engine. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_pool_size
description: Number of threads to perform merges and mutations in background. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_merges_mutations_concurrency_ratio
description: Ratio between a number of how many operations could be processed and a number threads to process them. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_move_pool_size
description: Number of threads performing background moves for tables. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_fetches_pool_size
description: Number of threads performing background fetches for replicated tables. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_common_pool_size
description: Number of threads for some lightweight tasks for replicated tables (like cleaning old parts etc.). Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_schedule_pool_size
description: Number of threads performing background tasks for replicated tables, dns cache updates. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_message_broker_schedule_pool_size
description: Number of threads performing background tasks for message streaming. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: background_distributed_schedule_pool_size
description: Number of threads performing background tasks for distributed sends. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: max_replicated_fetches_network_bandwidth_for_server
description: The maximum speed of data exchange over the network in bytes per second for replicated fetches. Zero means unlimited. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: max_replicated_sends_network_bandwidth_for_server
description: The maximum speed of data exchange over the network in bytes per second for replicated sends. Zero means unlimited. Only has meaning at server startup.

name: distributed_directory_monitor_sleep_time_ms
description: Sleep time for StorageDistributed DirectoryMonitors, in case of any errors delay grows exponentially.

name: distributed_directory_monitor_max_sleep_time_ms
description: Maximum sleep time for StorageDistributed DirectoryMonitors, it limits exponential growth too.

name: distributed_directory_monitor_batch_inserts
description: Should StorageDistributed DirectoryMonitors try to batch individual inserts into bigger ones.

name: distributed_directory_monitor_split_batch_on_failure
description: Should StorageDistributed DirectoryMonitors try to split batch into smaller in case of failures.

name: optimize_move_to_prewhere
description: Allows disabling WHERE to PREWHERE optimization in SELECT queries from MergeTree.

name: optimize_move_to_prewhere_if_final
description: If query has `FINAL`, the optimization `move_to_prewhere` is not always correct and it is enabled only if both settings `optimize_move_to_prewhere` and `optimize_move_to_prewhere_if_final` are turned on

name: replication_alter_partitions_sync
description: Wait for actions to manipulate the partitions. 0 - do not wait, 1 - wait for execution only of itself, 2 - wait for everyone.

name: replication_wait_for_inactive_replica_timeout
description: Wait for inactive replica to execute ALTER/OPTIMIZE. Time in seconds, 0 - do not wait, negative - wait for unlimited time.

name: load_balancing
description: Which replicas (among healthy replicas) to preferably send a query to (on the first attempt) for distributed processing.

name: load_balancing_first_offset
description: Which replica to preferably send a query when FIRST_OR_RANDOM load balancing strategy is used.

name: totals_mode
description: How to calculate TOTALS when HAVING is present, as well as when max_rows_to_group_by and group_by_overflow_mode = ‘any’ are present.

name: totals_auto_threshold
description: The threshold for totals_mode = 'auto'.

name: allow_suspicious_low_cardinality_types
description: In CREATE TABLE statement allows specifying LowCardinality modifier for types of small fixed size (8 or less). Enabling this may increase merge times and memory consumption.

name: compile_expressions
description: Compile some scalar functions and operators to native code.

name: min_count_to_compile_expression
description: The number of identical expressions before they are JIT-compiled

name: compile_aggregate_expressions
description: Compile aggregate functions to native code.

name: min_count_to_compile_aggregate_expression
description: The number of identical aggregate expressions before they are JIT-compiled

name: group_by_two_level_threshold
description: From what number of keys, a two-level aggregation starts. 0 - the threshold is not set.

name: group_by_two_level_threshold_bytes
description: From what size of the aggregation state in bytes, a two-level aggregation begins to be used. 0 - the threshold is not set. Two-level aggregation is used when at least one of the thresholds is triggered.

name: distributed_aggregation_memory_efficient
description: Is the memory-saving mode of distributed aggregation enabled.

name: aggregation_memory_efficient_merge_threads
description: Number of threads to use for merge intermediate aggregation results in memory efficient mode. When bigger, then more memory is consumed. 0 means - same as 'max_threads'.

name: enable_positional_arguments
description: Enable positional arguments in ORDER BY, GROUP BY and LIMIT BY

name: max_parallel_replicas
description: The maximum number of replicas of each shard used when the query is executed. For consistency (to get different parts of the same partition), this option only works for the specified sampling key. The lag of the replicas is not controlled.

name: skip_unavailable_shards
description: If true, ClickHouse silently skips unavailable shards and nodes unresolvable through DNS. Shard is marked as unavailable when none of the replicas can be reached.

name: parallel_distributed_insert_select
description: Process distributed INSERT SELECT query in the same cluster on local tables on every shard, if 1 SELECT is executed on each shard, if 2 SELECT and INSERT is executed on each shard

name: distributed_group_by_no_merge
description: If 1, Do not merge aggregation states from different servers for distributed queries (shards will process query up to the Complete stage, initiator just proxies the data from the shards). If 2 the initiator will apply ORDER BY and LIMIT stages (it is not in case when shard process query up to the Complete stage)

name: distributed_push_down_limit
description: If 1, LIMIT will be applied on each shard separatelly. Usually you don't need to use it, since this will be done automatically if it is possible, i.e. for simple query SELECT FROM LIMIT.

name: optimize_distributed_group_by_sharding_key
description: Optimize GROUP BY sharding_key queries (by avoiding costly aggregation on the initiator server).

name: optimize_skip_unused_shards_limit
description: Limit for number of sharding key values, turns off optimize_skip_unused_shards if the limit is reached

name: optimize_skip_unused_shards
description: Assumes that data is distributed by sharding_key. Optimization to skip unused shards if SELECT query filters by sharding_key.

name: optimize_skip_unused_shards_rewrite_in
description: Rewrite IN in query for remote shards to exclude values that does not belong to the shard (requires optimize_skip_unused_shards)

name: allow_nondeterministic_optimize_skip_unused_shards
description: Allow non-deterministic functions (includes dictGet) in sharding_key for optimize_skip_unused_shards

name: force_optimize_skip_unused_shards
description: Throw an exception if unused shards cannot be skipped (1 - throw only if the table has the sharding key, 2 - always throw.

name: optimize_skip_unused_shards_nesting
description: Same as optimize_skip_unused_shards, but accept nesting level until which it will work.

name: force_optimize_skip_unused_shards_nesting
description: Same as force_optimize_skip_unused_shards, but accept nesting level until which it will work.

name: input_format_parallel_parsing
description: Enable parallel parsing for some data formats.

name: min_chunk_bytes_for_parallel_parsing
description: The minimum chunk size in bytes, which each thread will parse in parallel.

name: output_format_parallel_formatting
description: Enable parallel formatting for some data formats.

name: merge_tree_min_rows_for_concurrent_read
description: If at least as many lines are read from one file, the reading can be parallelized.

name: merge_tree_min_bytes_for_concurrent_read
description: If at least as many bytes are read from one file, the reading can be parallelized.

name: merge_tree_min_rows_for_seek
description: You can skip reading more than that number of rows at the price of one seek per file.

name: merge_tree_min_bytes_for_seek
description: You can skip reading more than that number of bytes at the price of one seek per file.

name: merge_tree_coarse_index_granularity
description: If the index segment can contain the required keys, divide it into as many parts and recursively check them.

name: merge_tree_max_rows_to_use_cache
description: The maximum number of rows per request, to use the cache of uncompressed data. If the request is large, the cache is not used. (For large queries not to flush out the cache.)

name: merge_tree_max_bytes_to_use_cache
description: The maximum number of bytes per request, to use the cache of uncompressed data. If the request is large, the cache is not used. (For large queries not to flush out the cache.)

name: merge_tree_clear_old_temporary_directories_interval_seconds
description: The period of executing the clear old temporary directories operation in background.

name: merge_tree_clear_old_parts_interval_seconds
description: The period of executing the clear old parts operation in background.

name: do_not_merge_across_partitions_select_final
description: Merge parts only in one partition in select final

name: mysql_max_rows_to_insert
description: The maximum number of rows in MySQL batch insertion of the MySQL storage engine

name: optimize_min_equality_disjunction_chain_length
description: The minimum length of the expression `expr = x1 OR ... expr = xN` for optimization

name: min_bytes_to_use_direct_io
description: The minimum number of bytes for reading the data with O_DIRECT option during SELECT queries execution. 0 - disabled.

name: min_bytes_to_use_mmap_io
description: The minimum number of bytes for reading the data with mmap option during SELECT queries execution. 0 - disabled.

name: checksum_on_read
description: Validate checksums on reading. It is enabled by default and should be always enabled in production. Please do not expect any benefits in disabling this setting. It may only be used for experiments and benchmarks. The setting only applicable for tables of MergeTree family. Checksums are always validated for other table engines and when receiving data over network.

name: force_index_by_date
description: Throw an exception if there is a partition key in a table, and it is not used.

name: force_primary_key
description: Throw an exception if there is primary key in a table, and it is not used.

name: use_skip_indexes
description: Use data skipping indexes during query execution.

name: force_data_skipping_indices
description: Comma separated list of strings or literals with the name of the data skipping indices that should be used during query execution, otherwise an exception will be thrown.

name: max_streams_to_max_threads_ratio
description: Allows you to use more sources than the number of threads - to more evenly distribute work across threads. It is assumed that this is a temporary solution, since it will be possible in the future to make the number of sources equal to the number of threads, but for each source to dynamically select available work for itself.

name: max_streams_multiplier_for_merge_tables
description: Ask more streams when reading from Merge table. Streams will be spread across tables that Merge table will use. This allows more even distribution of work across threads and especially helpful when merged tables differ in size.

name: network_compression_method
description: Allows you to select the method of data compression when writing.

name: network_zstd_compression_level
description: Allows you to select the level of ZSTD compression.

name: priority
description: Priority of the query. 1 - the highest, higher value - lower priority; 0 - do not use priorities.

name: os_thread_priority
description: If non zero - set corresponding 'nice' value for query processing threads. Can be used to adjust query priority for OS scheduler.

name: log_queries
description: Log requests and write the log to the system table.

name: log_formatted_queries
description: Log formatted queries and write the log to the system table.

name: log_queries_min_type
description: Minimal type in query_log to log, possible values (from low to high): QUERY_START, QUERY_FINISH, EXCEPTION_BEFORE_START, EXCEPTION_WHILE_PROCESSING.

name: log_queries_min_query_duration_ms
description: Minimal time for the query to run, to get to the query_log/query_thread_log/query_views_log.

name: log_queries_cut_to_length
description: If query length is greater than specified threshold (in bytes), then cut query when writing to query log. Also limit length of printed query in ordinary text log.

name: log_queries_probability
description: Log queries with the specified probabality.

name: distributed_product_mode
description: How are distributed subqueries performed inside IN or JOIN sections?

name: max_concurrent_queries_for_all_users
description: The maximum number of concurrent requests for all users.

name: max_concurrent_queries_for_user
description: The maximum number of concurrent requests per user.

name: insert_deduplicate
description: For INSERT queries in the replicated table, specifies that deduplication of insertings blocks should be performed

name: insert_quorum
description: For INSERT queries in the replicated table, wait writing for the specified number of replicas and linearize the addition of the data. 0 - disabled.

name: insert_quorum_parallel
description: For quorum INSERT queries - enable to make parallel inserts without linearizability

name: select_sequential_consistency
description: For SELECT queries from the replicated table, throw an exception if the replica does not have a chunk written with the quorum; do not read the parts that have not yet been written with the quorum.

name: table_function_remote_max_addresses
description: The maximum number of different shards and the maximum number of replicas of one shard in the `remote` function.

name: read_backoff_min_latency_ms
description: Setting to reduce the number of threads in case of slow reads. Pay attention only to reads that took at least that much time.

name: read_backoff_max_throughput
description: Settings to reduce the number of threads in case of slow reads. Count events when the read bandwidth is less than that many bytes per second.

name: read_backoff_min_interval_between_events_ms
description: Settings to reduce the number of threads in case of slow reads. Do not pay attention to the event, if the previous one has passed less than a certain amount of time.

name: read_backoff_min_events
description: Settings to reduce the number of threads in case of slow reads. The number of events after which the number of threads will be reduced.

name: read_backoff_min_concurrency
description: Settings to try keeping the minimal number of threads in case of slow reads.

name: memory_tracker_fault_probability
description: For testing of `exception safety` - throw an exception every time you allocate memory with the specified probability.

name: enable_http_compression
description: Compress the result if the client over HTTP said that it understands data compressed by gzip or deflate.

name: http_zlib_compression_level
description: Compression level - used if the client on HTTP said that it understands data compressed by gzip or deflate.

name: http_native_compression_disable_checksumming_on_decompress
description: If you uncompress the POST data from the client compressed by the native format, do not check the checksum.

name: count_distinct_implementation
description: What aggregate function to use for implementation of count(DISTINCT ...)

name: add_http_cors_header
description: Write add http CORS header.

name: max_http_get_redirects
description: Max number of http GET redirects hops allowed. Make sure additional security measures are in place to prevent a malicious server to redirect your requests to unexpected services.

name: use_client_time_zone
description: Use client timezone for interpreting DateTime string values, instead of adopting server timezone.

name: send_progress_in_http_headers
description: Send progress notifications using X-ClickHouse-Progress headers. Some clients do not support high amount of HTTP headers (Python requests in particular), so it is disabled by default.

name: http_headers_progress_interval_ms
description: Do not send HTTP headers X-ClickHouse-Progress more frequently than at each specified interval.

name: fsync_metadata
description: Do fsync after changing metadata for tables and databases (.sql files). Could be disabled in case of poor latency on server with high load of DDL queries and high load of disk subsystem.

name: join_use_nulls
description: Use NULLs for non-joined rows of outer JOINs for types that can be inside Nullable. If false, use default value of corresponding columns data type.

name: join_default_strictness
description: Set default strictness in JOIN query. Possible values: empty string, 'ANY', 'ALL'. If empty, query without strictness will throw exception.

name: any_join_distinct_right_table_keys
description: Enable old ANY JOIN logic with many-to-one left-to-right table keys mapping for all ANY JOINs. It leads to confusing not equal results for 't1 ANY LEFT JOIN t2' and 't2 ANY RIGHT JOIN t1'. ANY RIGHT JOIN needs one-to-many keys mapping to be consistent with LEFT one.

name: max_replica_delay_for_distributed_queries
description: If set, distributed queries of Replicated tables will choose servers with replication delay in seconds less than the specified value (not inclusive). Zero means do not take delay into account.

name: fallback_to_stale_replicas_for_distributed_queries
description: Suppose max_replica_delay_for_distributed_queries is set and all replicas for the queried table are stale. If this setting is enabled, the query will be performed anyway, otherwise the error will be reported.

name: preferred_max_column_in_block_size_bytes
description: Limit on max column size in block while reading. Helps to decrease cache misses count. Should be close to L2 cache size.

name: insert_distributed_sync
description: If setting is enabled, insert query into distributed waits until data will be sent to all nodes in cluster.

name: insert_distributed_timeout
description: Timeout for insert query into distributed. Setting is used only with insert_distributed_sync enabled. Zero value means no timeout.

name: distributed_ddl_task_timeout
description: Timeout for DDL query responses from all hosts in cluster. If a ddl request has not been performed on all hosts, a response will contain a timeout error and a request will be executed in an async mode. Negative value means infinite. Zero means async mode.

name: stream_flush_interval_ms
description: Timeout for flushing data from streaming storages.

name: stream_poll_timeout_ms
description: Timeout for polling data from/to streaming storages.

name: sleep_in_send_tables_status_ms
description: Time to sleep in sending tables status response in TCPHandler

name: sleep_in_send_data_ms
description: Time to sleep in sending data in TCPHandler

name: unknown_packet_in_send_data
description: Send unknown packet instead of data Nth data packet

name: sleep_in_receive_cancel_ms
description: Time to sleep in receiving cancel in TCPHandler

name: insert_allow_materialized_columns
description: If setting is enabled, Allow materialized columns in INSERT.

name: http_connection_timeout
description: HTTP connection timeout.

name: http_send_timeout
description: HTTP send timeout

name: http_receive_timeout
description: HTTP receive timeout

name: http_max_uri_size
description: Maximum URI length of HTTP request

name: http_max_fields
description: Maximum number of fields in HTTP header

name: http_max_field_name_size
description: Maximum length of field name in HTTP header

name: http_max_field_value_size
description: Maximum length of field value in HTTP header

name: optimize_throw_if_noop
description: If setting is enabled and OPTIMIZE query didn't actually assign a merge then an explanatory exception is thrown

name: use_index_for_in_with_subqueries
description: Try using an index if there is a subquery or a table expression on the right side of the IN operator.

name: joined_subquery_requires_alias
description: Force joined subqueries and table functions to have aliases for correct name qualification.

name: empty_result_for_aggregation_by_empty_set
description: Return empty result when aggregating without keys on empty set.

name: empty_result_for_aggregation_by_constant_keys_on_empty_set
description: Return empty result when aggregating by constant keys on empty set.

name: allow_distributed_ddl
description: If it is set to true, then a user is allowed to executed distributed DDL queries.

name: allow_suspicious_codecs
description: If it is set to true, allow to specify meaningless compression codecs.

name: allow_experimental_codecs
description: If it is set to true, allow to specify experimental compression codecs (but we don't have those yet and this option does nothing).

name: query_profiler_real_time_period_ns
description: Period for real clock timer of query profiler (in nanoseconds). Set 0 value to turn off the real clock query profiler. Recommended value is at least 10000000 (100 times a second) for single queries or 1000000000 (once a second) for cluster-wide profiling.

name: query_profiler_cpu_time_period_ns
description: Period for CPU clock timer of query profiler (in nanoseconds). Set 0 value to turn off the CPU clock query profiler. Recommended value is at least 10000000 (100 times a second) for single queries or 1000000000 (once a second) for cluster-wide profiling.

name: metrics_perf_events_enabled
description: If enabled, some of the perf events will be measured throughout queries' execution.

name: metrics_perf_events_list
description: Comma separated list of perf metrics that will be measured throughout queries' execution. Empty means all events. See PerfEventInfo in sources for the available events.

name: opentelemetry_start_trace_probability
description: Probability to start an OpenTelemetry trace for an incoming query.

name: prefer_column_name_to_alias
description: Prefer using column names instead of aliases if possible.

name: prefer_global_in_and_join
description: If enabled, all IN/JOIN operators will be rewritten as GLOBAL IN/JOIN. It's useful when the to-be-joined tables are only available on the initiator and we need to always scatter their data on-the-fly during distributed processing with the GLOBAL keyword. It's also useful to reduce the need to access the external sources joining external tables.

name: max_rows_to_read
description: Limit on read rows from the most 'deep' sources. That is, only in the deepest subquery. When reading from a remote server, it is only checked on a remote server.

name: max_bytes_to_read
description: Limit on read bytes (after decompression) from the most 'deep' sources. That is, only in the deepest subquery. When reading from a remote server, it is only checked on a remote server.

name: read_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: max_rows_to_read_leaf
description: Limit on read rows on the leaf nodes for distributed queries. Limit is applied for local reads only excluding the final merge stage on the root node.

name: max_bytes_to_read_leaf
description: Limit on read bytes (after decompression) on the leaf nodes for distributed queries. Limit is applied for local reads only excluding the final merge stage on the root node.

name: read_overflow_mode_leaf
description: What to do when the leaf limit is exceeded.

name: group_by_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: sort_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: max_bytes_before_remerge_sort
description: In case of ORDER BY with LIMIT, when memory usage is higher than specified threshold, perform additional steps of merging blocks before final merge to keep just top LIMIT rows.

name: remerge_sort_lowered_memory_bytes_ratio
description: If memory usage after remerge does not reduced by this ratio, remerge will be disabled.

name: max_result_rows
description: Limit on result size in rows. Also checked for intermediate data sent from remote servers.

name: max_result_bytes
description: Limit on result size in bytes (uncompressed). Also checked for intermediate data sent from remote servers.

name: result_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: timeout_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: min_execution_speed
description: Minimum number of execution rows per second.

name: max_execution_speed
description: Maximum number of execution rows per second.

name: min_execution_speed_bytes
description: Minimum number of execution bytes per second.

name: max_execution_speed_bytes
description: Maximum number of execution bytes per second.

name: timeout_before_checking_execution_speed
description: Check that the speed is not too low after the specified time has elapsed.

name: max_ast_depth
description: Maximum depth of query syntax tree. Checked after parsing.

name: max_ast_elements
description: Maximum size of query syntax tree in number of nodes. Checked after parsing.

name: max_expanded_ast_elements
description: Maximum size of query syntax tree in number of nodes after expansion of aliases and the asterisk.

name: readonly
description: 0 - everything is allowed. 1 - only read requests. 2 - only read requests, as well as changing settings, except for the 'readonly' setting.

name: max_rows_in_set
description: Maximum size of the set (in number of elements) resulting from the execution of the IN section.

name: max_bytes_in_set
description: Maximum size of the set (in bytes in memory) resulting from the execution of the IN section.

name: set_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: max_rows_in_join
description: Maximum size of the hash table for JOIN (in number of rows).

name: max_bytes_in_join
description: Maximum size of the hash table for JOIN (in number of bytes in memory).

name: join_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: join_any_take_last_row
description: When disabled (default) ANY JOIN will take the first found row for a key. When enabled, it will take the last row seen if there are multiple rows for the same key.

name: join_algorithm
description: Specify join algorithm: 'auto', 'hash', 'partial_merge', 'prefer_partial_merge'. 'auto' tries to change HashJoin to MergeJoin on the fly to avoid out of memory.

name: partial_merge_join_optimizations
description: Enable optimizations in partial merge join

name: default_max_bytes_in_join
description: Maximum size of right-side table if limit is required but max_bytes_in_join is not set.

name: partial_merge_join_left_table_buffer_bytes
description: If not 0 group left table blocks in bigger ones for left-side table in partial merge join. It uses up to 2x of specified memory per joining thread. In current version work only with 'partial_merge_join_optimizations = 1'.

name: partial_merge_join_rows_in_right_blocks
description: Split right-hand joining data in blocks of specified size. It's a portion of data indexed by min-max values and possibly unloaded on disk.

name: join_on_disk_max_files_to_merge
description: For MergeJoin on disk set how much files it's allowed to sort simultaneously. Then this value bigger then more memory used and then less disk I/O needed. Minimum is 2.

name: temporary_files_codec
description: Set compression codec for temporary files (sort and join on disk). I.e. LZ4, NONE.

name: max_rows_to_transfer
description: Maximum size (in rows) of the transmitted external table obtained when the GLOBAL IN/JOIN section is executed.

name: max_bytes_to_transfer
description: Maximum size (in uncompressed bytes) of the transmitted external table obtained when the GLOBAL IN/JOIN section is executed.

name: transfer_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: max_rows_in_distinct
description: Maximum number of elements during execution of DISTINCT.

name: max_bytes_in_distinct
description: Maximum total size of state (in uncompressed bytes) in memory for the execution of DISTINCT.

name: distinct_overflow_mode
description: What to do when the limit is exceeded.

name: max_memory_usage
description: Maximum memory usage for processing of single query. Zero means unlimited.

name: max_memory_usage_for_user
description: Maximum memory usage for processing all concurrently running queries for the user. Zero means unlimited.

name: max_untracked_memory
description: Small allocations and deallocations are grouped in thread local variable and tracked or profiled only when amount (in absolute value) becomes larger than specified value. If the value is higher than 'memory_profiler_step' it will be effectively lowered to 'memory_profiler_step'.

name: memory_profiler_step
description: Whenever query memory usage becomes larger than every next step in number of bytes the memory profiler will collect the allocating stack trace. Zero means disabled memory profiler. Values lower than a few megabytes will slow down query processing.

name: memory_profiler_sample_probability
description: Collect random allocations and deallocations and write them into system.trace_log with 'MemorySample' trace_type. The probability is for every alloc/free regardless to the size of the allocation. Note that sampling happens only when the amount of untracked memory exceeds 'max_untracked_memory'. You may want to set 'max_untracked_memory' to 0 for extra fine grained sampling.

name: max_network_bandwidth
description: The maximum speed of data exchange over the network in bytes per second for a query. Zero means unlimited.

name: max_network_bytes
description: The maximum number of bytes (compressed) to receive or transmit over the network for execution of the query.

name: max_network_bandwidth_for_user
description: The maximum speed of data exchange over the network in bytes per second for all concurrently running user queries. Zero means unlimited.

name: max_network_bandwidth_for_all_users
description: The maximum speed of data exchange over the network in bytes per second for all concurrently running queries. Zero means unlimited.

name: max_backup_threads
description: The maximum number of threads to execute a BACKUP or RESTORE request. By default, it is determined automatically.

name: log_profile_events
description: Log query performance statistics into the query_log, query_thread_log and query_views_log.

name: log_query_settings
description: Log query settings into the query_log.

name: log_query_threads
description: Log query threads into system.query_thread_log table. This setting have effect only when 'log_queries' is true.

name: log_query_views
description: Log query dependent views into system.query_views_log table. This setting have effect only when 'log_queries' is true.

name: log_comment
description: Log comment into system.query_log table and server log. It can be set to arbitrary string no longer than max_query_size.

name: send_logs_level
description: Send server text logs with specified minimum level to client. Valid values: 'trace', 'debug', 'information', 'warning', 'error', 'fatal', 'none'

name: enable_optimize_predicate_expression
description: If it is set to true, optimize predicates to subqueries.

name: enable_optimize_predicate_expression_to_final_subquery
description: Allow push predicate to final subquery.

name: allow_push_predicate_when_subquery_contains_with
description: Allows push predicate when subquery contains WITH clause

name: low_cardinality_max_dictionary_size
description: Maximum size (in rows) of shared global dictionary for LowCardinality type.

name: low_cardinality_use_single_dictionary_for_part
description: LowCardinality type serialization setting. If is true, than will use additional keys when global dictionary overflows. Otherwise, will create several shared dictionaries.

name: decimal_check_overflow
description: Check overflow of decimal arithmetic/comparison operations

name: prefer_localhost_replica
description: If it's true then queries will be always sent to local replica (if it exists). If it's false then replica to send a query will be chosen between local and remote ones according to load_balancing

name: max_fetch_partition_retries_count
description: Amount of retries while fetching partition from another host.

name: http_max_multipart_form_data_size
description: Limit on size of multipart/form-data content. This setting cannot be parsed from URL parameters and should be set in user profile. Note that content is parsed and external tables are created in memory before start of query execution. And this is the only limit that has effect on that stage (limits on max memory usage and max execution time have no effect while reading HTTP form data).

name: calculate_text_stack_trace
description: Calculate text stack trace in case of exceptions during query execution. This is the default. It requires symbol lookups that may slow down fuzzing tests when huge amount of wrong queries are executed. In normal cases you should not disable this option.

name: allow_ddl
description: If it is set to true, then a user is allowed to executed DDL queries.

name: parallel_view_processing
description: Enables pushing to attached views concurrently instead of sequentially.

name: enable_unaligned_array_join
description: Allow ARRAY JOIN with multiple arrays that have different sizes. When this settings is enabled, arrays will be resized to the longest one.

name: optimize_read_in_order
description: Enable ORDER BY optimization for reading data in corresponding order in MergeTree tables.

name: optimize_aggregation_in_order
description: Enable GROUP BY optimization for aggregating data in corresponding order in MergeTree tables.

name: aggregation_in_order_max_block_bytes
description: Maximal size of block in bytes accumulated during aggregation in order of primary key. Lower block size allows to parallelize more final merge stage of aggregation.

name: read_in_order_two_level_merge_threshold
description: Minimal number of parts to read to run preliminary merge step during multithread reading in order of primary key.

name: low_cardinality_allow_in_native_format
description: Use LowCardinality type in Native format. Otherwise, convert LowCardinality columns to ordinary for select query, and convert ordinary columns to required LowCardinality for insert query.

name: cancel_http_readonly_queries_on_client_close
description: Cancel HTTP readonly queries when a client closes the connection without waiting for response.

name: external_table_functions_use_nulls
description: If it is set to true, external table functions will implicitly use Nullable type if needed. Otherwise NULLs will be substituted with default values. Currently supported only by 'mysql', 'postgresql' and 'odbc' table functions.

name: external_table_strict_query
description: If it is set to true, transforming expression to local filter is forbidden for queries to external tables.

name: allow_hyperscan
description: Allow functions that use Hyperscan library. Disable to avoid potentially long compilation times and excessive resource usage.

name: max_hyperscan_regexp_length
description: Max length of regexp than can be used in hyperscan multi-match functions. Zero means unlimited.

name: max_hyperscan_regexp_total_length
description: Max total length of all regexps than can be used in hyperscan multi-match functions (per every function). Zero means unlimited.

name: allow_simdjson
description: Allow using simdjson library in 'JSON*' functions if AVX2 instructions are available. If disabled rapidjson will be used.

name: allow_introspection_functions
description: Allow functions for introspection of ELF and DWARF for query profiling. These functions are slow and may impose security considerations.

name: max_partitions_per_insert_block
description: Limit maximum number of partitions in single INSERTed block. Zero means unlimited. Throw exception if the block contains too many partitions. This setting is a safety threshold, because using large number of partitions is a common misconception.

name: max_partitions_to_read
description: Limit the max number of partitions that can be accessed in one query. <= 0 means unlimited.

name: check_query_single_value_result
description: Return check query result as single 1/0 value

name: allow_drop_detached
description: Allow ALTER TABLE ... DROP DETACHED PART[ITION] ... queries

name: postgresql_connection_pool_size
description: Connection pool size for PostgreSQL table engine and database engine.

name: postgresql_connection_pool_wait_timeout
description: Connection pool push/pop timeout on empty pool for PostgreSQL table engine and database engine. By default it will block on empty pool.

name: glob_expansion_max_elements
description: Maximum number of allowed addresses (For external storages, table functions, etc).

name: odbc_bridge_connection_pool_size
description: Connection pool size for each connection settings string in ODBC bridge.

name: distributed_replica_error_half_life
description: Time period reduces replica error counter by 2 times.

name: distributed_replica_error_cap
description: Max number of errors per replica, prevents piling up an incredible amount of errors if replica was offline for some time and allows it to be reconsidered in a shorter amount of time.

name: distributed_replica_max_ignored_errors
description: Number of errors that will be ignored while choosing replicas

name: allow_experimental_live_view
description: Enable LIVE VIEW. Not mature enough.

name: live_view_heartbeat_interval
description: The heartbeat interval in seconds to indicate live query is alive.

name: max_live_view_insert_blocks_before_refresh
description: Limit maximum number of inserted blocks after which mergeable blocks are dropped and query is re-executed.

name: min_free_disk_space_for_temporary_data
description: The minimum disk space to keep while writing temporary data used in external sorting and aggregation.

name: default_database_engine
description: Default database engine.

name: show_table_uuid_in_table_create_query_if_not_nil
description: For tables in databases with Engine=Atomic show UUID of the table in its CREATE query.

name: database_atomic_wait_for_drop_and_detach_synchronously
description: When executing DROP or DETACH TABLE in Atomic database, wait for table data to be finally dropped or detached.

name: enable_scalar_subquery_optimization
description: If it is set to true, prevent scalar subqueries from (de)serializing large scalar values and possibly avoid running the same subquery more than once.

name: optimize_trivial_count_query
description: Process trivial 'SELECT count() FROM table' query from metadata.

name: optimize_respect_aliases
description: If it is set to true, it will respect aliases in WHERE/GROUP BY/ORDER BY, that will help with partition pruning/secondary indexes/optimize_aggregation_in_order/optimize_read_in_order/optimize_trivial_count

name: mutations_sync
description: Wait for synchronous execution of ALTER TABLE UPDATE/DELETE queries (mutations). 0 - execute asynchronously. 1 - wait current server. 2 - wait all replicas if they exist.

name: optimize_move_functions_out_of_any
description: Move functions out of aggregate functions 'any', 'anyLast'.

name: optimize_normalize_count_variants
description: Rewrite aggregate functions that semantically equals to count() as count().

name: optimize_injective_functions_inside_uniq
description: Delete injective functions of one argument inside uniq*() functions.

name: optimize_arithmetic_operations_in_aggregate_functions
description: Move arithmetic operations out of aggregation functions

name: optimize_duplicate_order_by_and_distinct
description: Remove duplicate ORDER BY and DISTINCT if it's possible

name: optimize_redundant_functions_in_order_by
description: Remove functions from ORDER BY if its argument is also in ORDER BY

name: optimize_if_chain_to_multiif
description: Replace if(cond1, then1, if(cond2, ...)) chains to multiIf. Currently it's not beneficial for numeric types.

name: optimize_if_transform_strings_to_enum
description: Replaces string-type arguments in If and Transform to enum. Disabled by default cause it could make inconsistent change in distributed query that would lead to its fail.

name: optimize_monotonous_functions_in_order_by
description: Replace monotonous function with its argument in ORDER BY

name: optimize_functions_to_subcolumns
description: Transform functions to subcolumns, if possible, to reduce amount of read data. E.g. 'length(arr)' -> 'arr.size0', 'col IS NULL' -> 'col.null'

name: normalize_function_names
description: Normalize function names to their canonical names

name: allow_experimental_alter_materialized_view_structure
description: Allow atomic alter on Materialized views. Work in progress.

name: enable_early_constant_folding
description: Enable query optimization where we analyze function and subqueries results and rewrite query if there're constants there

name: deduplicate_blocks_in_dependent_materialized_views
description: Should deduplicate blocks for materialized views if the block is not a duplicate for the table. Use true to always deduplicate in dependent tables.

name: use_compact_format_in_distributed_parts_names
description: Changes format of directories names for distributed table insert parts.

name: validate_polygons
description: Throw exception if polygon is invalid in function pointInPolygon (e.g. self-tangent, self-intersecting). If the setting is false, the function will accept invalid polygons but may silently return wrong result.

name: max_parser_depth
description: Maximum parser depth (recursion depth of recursive descend parser).

name: temporary_live_view_timeout
description: Timeout after which temporary live view is deleted.

name: periodic_live_view_refresh
description: Interval after which periodically refreshed live view is forced to refresh.

name: transform_null_in
description: If enabled, NULL values will be matched with 'IN' operator as if they are considered equal.

name: allow_nondeterministic_mutations
description: Allow non-deterministic functions in ALTER UPDATE/ALTER DELETE statements

name: lock_acquire_timeout
description: How long locking request should wait before failing

name: materialize_ttl_after_modify
description: Apply TTL for old data, after ALTER MODIFY TTL query

name: function_implementation
description: Choose function implementation for specific target or variant (experimental). If empty enable all of them.

name: allow_experimental_geo_types
description: Allow geo data types such as Point, Ring, Polygon, MultiPolygon

name: data_type_default_nullable
description: Data types without NULL or NOT NULL will make Nullable

name: cast_keep_nullable
description: CAST operator keep Nullable for result data type

name: alter_partition_verbose_result
description: Output information about affected parts. Currently works only for FREEZE and ATTACH commands.

name: allow_experimental_database_materialized_mysql
description: Allow to create database with Engine=MaterializedMySQL(...).

name: allow_experimental_database_materialized_postgresql
description: Allow to create database with Engine=MaterializedPostgreSQL(...).

name: system_events_show_zero_values
description: Include all metrics, even with zero values

name: mysql_datatypes_support_level
description: Which MySQL types should be converted to corresponding ClickHouse types (rather than being represented as String). Can be empty or any combination of 'decimal' or 'datetime64'. When empty MySQL's DECIMAL and DATETIME/TIMESTAMP with non-zero precision are seen as String on ClickHouse's side.

name: optimize_trivial_insert_select
description: Optimize trivial 'INSERT INTO table SELECT ... FROM TABLES' query

name: allow_non_metadata_alters
description: Allow to execute alters which affects not only tables metadata, but also data on disk

name: enable_global_with_statement
description: Propagate WITH statements to UNION queries and all subqueries

name: aggregate_functions_null_for_empty
description: Rewrite all aggregate functions in a query, adding -OrNull suffix to them

name: optimize_syntax_fuse_functions
description: Fuse aggregate functions (`sum, avg, count` with identical arguments into one `sumCount`, quantile-family functions with the same argument into `quantiles*(...)[...]`)

name: flatten_nested
description: If true, columns of type Nested will be flatten to separate array columns instead of one array of tuples

name: asterisk_include_materialized_columns
description: Include MATERIALIZED columns for wildcard query

name: asterisk_include_alias_columns
description: Include ALIAS columns for wildcard query

name: optimize_skip_merged_partitions
description: Skip partitions with one part with level > 0 in optimize final

name: optimize_on_insert
description: Do the same transformation for inserted block of data as if merge was done on this block.

name: allow_experimental_map_type
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: allow_experimental_projection_optimization
description: Enable projection optimization when processing SELECT queries

name: force_optimize_projection
description: If projection optimization is enabled, SELECT queries need to use projection

name: async_socket_for_remote
description: Asynchronously read from socket executing remote query

name: insert_null_as_default
description: Insert DEFAULT values instead of NULL in INSERT SELECT (UNION ALL)

name: describe_include_subcolumns
description: If true, subcolumns of all table columns will be included into result of DESCRIBE query

name: optimize_rewrite_sum_if_to_count_if
description: Rewrite sumIf() and sum(if()) function countIf() function when logically equivalent

name: insert_shard_id
description: If non zero, when insert into a distributed table, the data will be inserted into the shard `insert_shard_id` synchronously. Possible values range from 1 to `shards_number` of corresponding distributed table

name: allow_experimental_query_deduplication
description: Experimental data deduplication for SELECT queries based on part UUIDs

name: experimental_query_deduplication_send_all_part_uuids
description: If false only part UUIDs for currently moving parts are sent. If true all read part UUIDs are sent (useful only for testing).

name: engine_file_empty_if_not_exists
description: Allows to select data from a file engine table without file

name: engine_file_truncate_on_insert
description: Enables or disables truncate before insert in file engine tables

name: allow_experimental_database_replicated
description: Allow to create databases with Replicated engine

name: database_replicated_initial_query_timeout_sec
description: How long initial DDL query should wait for Replicated database to precess previous DDL queue entries

name: max_distributed_depth
description: Maximum distributed query depth

name: database_replicated_always_detach_permanently
description: Execute DETACH TABLE as DETACH TABLE PERMANENTLY if database engine is Replicated

name: distributed_ddl_output_mode
description: Format of distributed DDL query result

name: distributed_ddl_entry_format_version
description: Version of DDL entry to write into ZooKeeper

name: external_storage_max_read_rows
description: Limit maximum number of rows when table with external engine should flush history data. Now supported only for MySQL table engine, database engine, dictionary and MaterializedMySQL. If equal to 0, this setting is disabled

name: external_storage_max_read_bytes
description: Limit maximum number of bytes when table with external engine should flush history data. Now supported only for MySQL table engine, database engine, dictionary and MaterializedMySQL. If equal to 0, this setting is disabled

name: union_default_mode
description: Set default Union Mode in SelectWithUnion query. Possible values: empty string, 'ALL', 'DISTINCT'. If empty, query without Union Mode will throw exception.

name: optimize_aggregators_of_group_by_keys
description: Eliminates min/max/any/anyLast aggregators of GROUP BY keys in SELECT section

name: optimize_group_by_function_keys
description: Eliminates functions of other keys in GROUP BY section

name: legacy_column_name_of_tuple_literal
description: List all names of element of large tuple literals in their column names instead of hash. This settings exists only for compatibility reasons. It makes sense to set to 'true', while doing rolling update of cluster from version lower than 21.7 to higher.

name: query_plan_enable_optimizations
description: Apply optimizations to query plan

name: query_plan_max_optimizations_to_apply
description: Limit the total number of optimizations applied to query plan. If zero, ignored. If limit reached, throw exception

name: query_plan_filter_push_down
description: Allow to push down filter by predicate query plan step

name: regexp_max_matches_per_row
description: Max matches of any single regexp per row, used to safeguard 'extractAllGroupsHorizontal' against consuming too much memory with greedy RE.

name: limit
description: Limit on read rows from the most 'end' result for select query, default 0 means no limit length

name: offset
description: Offset on read rows from the most 'end' result for select query

name: function_range_max_elements_in_block
description: Maximum number of values generated by function 'range' per block of data (sum of array sizes for every row in a block, see also 'max_block_size' and 'min_insert_block_size_rows'). It is a safety threshold.

name: short_circuit_function_evaluation
description: Setting for short-circuit function evaluation configuration. Possible values: 'enable' - use short-circuit function evaluation for functions that are suitable for it, 'disable' - disable short-circuit function evaluation, 'force_enable' - use short-circuit function evaluation for all functions.

name: local_filesystem_read_method
description: Method of reading data from local filesystem, one of: read, pread, mmap, pread_threadpool.

name: remote_filesystem_read_method
description: Method of reading data from remote filesystem, one of: read, threadpool.

name: local_filesystem_read_prefetch
description: Should use prefetching when reading data from local filesystem.

name: remote_filesystem_read_prefetch
description: Should use prefetching when reading data from remote filesystem.

name: read_priority
description: Priority to read data from local filesystem. Only supported for 'pread_threadpool' method.

name: async_insert_threads
description: Maximum number of threads to actually parse and insert data in background. Zero means asynchronous mode is disabled

name: async_insert
description: If true, data from INSERT query is stored in queue and later flushed to table in background. Makes sense only for inserts via HTTP protocol. If wait_for_async_insert is false, INSERT query is processed almost instantly, otherwise client will wait until data will be flushed to table

name: wait_for_async_insert
description: If true wait for processing of asynchronous insertion

name: wait_for_async_insert_timeout
description: Timeout for waiting for processing asynchronous insertion

name: async_insert_max_data_size
description: Maximum size in bytes of unparsed data collected per query before being inserted

name: async_insert_busy_timeout_ms
description: Maximum time to wait before dumping collected data per query since the first data appeared

name: async_insert_stale_timeout_ms
description: Maximum time to wait before dumping collected data per query since the last data appeared. Zero means no timeout at all

name: remote_fs_read_max_backoff_ms
description: Max wait time when trying to read data for remote disk

name: remote_fs_read_backoff_max_tries
description: Max attempts to read with backoff

name: force_remove_data_recursively_on_drop
description: Recursively remove data on DROP query. Avoids 'Directory not empty' error, but may silently remove detached data

name: allow_experimental_funnel_functions
description: Enable experimental functions for funnel analysis.

name: allow_experimental_nlp_functions
description: Enable experimental functions for natural language processing.

name: max_memory_usage_for_all_queries
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: multiple_joins_rewriter_version
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: enable_debug_queries
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: allow_experimental_database_atomic
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: allow_experimental_bigint_types
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: allow_experimental_window_functions
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: handle_kafka_error_mode
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: database_replicated_ddl_output
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: replication_alter_columns_timeout
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: optimize_fuse_sum_count_avg
description: Obsolete, use optimize_syntax_fuse_functions

name: odbc_max_field_size
description: Obsolete setting, does nothing.

name: format_csv_delimiter
description: The character to be considered as a delimiter in CSV data. If setting with a string, a string has to have a length of 1.

name: format_csv_allow_single_quotes
description: If it is set to true, allow strings in single quotes.

name: format_csv_allow_double_quotes
description: If it is set to true, allow strings in double quotes.

name: output_format_csv_crlf_end_of_line
description: If it is set true, end of line in CSV format will be \r\n instead of \n.

name: input_format_csv_unquoted_null_literal_as_null
description: Consider unquoted NULL literal as \N

name: input_format_csv_enum_as_number
description: Treat inserted enum values in CSV formats as enum indices \N

name: input_format_csv_arrays_as_nested_csv
description: When reading Array from CSV, expect that its elements were serialized in nested CSV and then put into string. Example: "[""Hello"", ""world"", ""42"""" TV""]". Braces around array can be omitted.

name: input_format_skip_unknown_fields
description: Skip columns with unknown names from input data (it works for JSONEachRow, CSVWithNames, TSVWithNames and TSKV formats).

name: input_format_with_names_use_header
description: For TSVWithNames and CSVWithNames input formats this controls whether format parser is to assume that column data appear in the input exactly as they are specified in the header.

name: input_format_import_nested_json
description: Map nested JSON data to nested tables (it works for JSONEachRow format).

name: input_format_defaults_for_omitted_fields
description: For input data calculate default expressions for omitted fields (it works for JSONEachRow, CSV and TSV formats).

name: input_format_tsv_empty_as_default
description: Treat empty fields in TSV input as default values.

name: input_format_tsv_enum_as_number
description: Treat inserted enum values in TSV formats as enum indices \N

name: input_format_null_as_default
description: For text input formats initialize null fields with default values if data type of this field is not nullable

name: input_format_arrow_import_nested
description: Allow to insert array of structs into Nested table in Arrow input format.

name: input_format_orc_import_nested
description: Allow to insert array of structs into Nested table in ORC input format.

name: input_format_parquet_import_nested
description: Allow to insert array of structs into Nested table in Parquet input format.

name: date_time_input_format
description: Method to read DateTime from text input formats. Possible values: 'basic' and 'best_effort'.

name: date_time_output_format
description: Method to write DateTime to text output. Possible values: 'simple', 'iso', 'unix_timestamp'.

name: input_format_values_interpret_expressions
description: For Values format: if the field could not be parsed by streaming parser, run SQL parser and try to interpret it as SQL expression.

name: input_format_values_deduce_templates_of_expressions
description: For Values format: if the field could not be parsed by streaming parser, run SQL parser, deduce template of the SQL expression, try to parse all rows using template and then interpret expression for all rows.

name: input_format_values_accurate_types_of_literals
description: For Values format: when parsing and interpreting expressions using template, check actual type of literal to avoid possible overflow and precision issues.

name: input_format_avro_allow_missing_fields
description: For Avro/AvroConfluent format: when field is not found in schema use default value instead of error

name: format_avro_schema_registry_url
description: For AvroConfluent format: Confluent Schema Registry URL.

name: output_format_avro_string_column_pattern
description: For Avro format: regexp of String columns to select as AVRO string.

name: output_format_json_quote_64bit_integers
description: Controls quoting of 64-bit integers in JSON output format.

name: output_format_json_quote_denormals
description: Enables '+nan', '-nan', '+inf', '-inf' outputs in JSON output format.

name: output_format_json_escape_forward_slashes
description: Controls escaping forward slashes for string outputs in JSON output format. This is intended for compatibility with JavaScript. Don't confuse with backslashes that are always escaped.

name: output_format_json_named_tuples_as_objects
description: Serialize named tuple columns as JSON objects.

name: output_format_json_array_of_rows
description: Output a JSON array of all rows in JSONEachRow(Compact) format.

name: output_format_pretty_max_rows
description: Rows limit for Pretty formats.

name: output_format_pretty_max_column_pad_width
description: Maximum width to pad all values in a column in Pretty formats.

name: output_format_pretty_max_value_width
description: Maximum width of value to display in Pretty formats. If greater - it will be cut.

name: output_format_pretty_color
description: Use ANSI escape sequences to paint colors in Pretty formats

name: output_format_pretty_grid_charset

description: Maximum relative amount of errors while reading text formats (like CSV, TSV). In case of error, if at least absolute or relative amount of errors is lower than corresponding value, will skip until next line and continue.
